text: The Parliament of Morocco (; ; ) is the bicameral legislature located in Rabat, the capital of Morocco. Since 1996, the national legislature has become bicameral and has two parliamentary chambers: * The House of Representatives or the lower house. 395 members elected directly for a five-year term. * The House of Councillorss 120 members are elected for a six-year term by two sets of electoral colleges. ==References== Category:Organizations based in Morocco
title: Parliament of Morocco
